Hey all,

I've added a new video file to the Files section of the Yahoo Group
(the Flash plug-in is required to view).

This weekend, Philip added a visual component to view the affinity
output of the eye as it scans the image canvass.

The video shows two circles, two squares, and two triangles being
viewed.  The upper left portion shows a top-level view of the eye
scanning the image.  The upper right shows what the eye is looking at.
 And the lower portion of the screen shows the affinity output during
scanning.  It ranges between 0 (non-match) and 1(match), and the
x-axis is the number of steps.

The affinity is actually calculated by taking the affinity value and
every step and summing the total, but values are skewed for outputs at
later steps.  This skewing is not reflected on the graph
shown...they're just raw affinity output values.

Have a look at let us know if you have any comments/questions.

Thanks,
Derek
